<br>
possible action of law against the makes of the blame is allready a pretty clear statement that the Game is blamed. <br>
<br>
Also, the only explanation that was given the mother didnt get the password to her sons charakter was:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
but they also are addicted and invariably hang up on her. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
With this statement they say that everyone addicted to a game was not capable to listen to a reasonable question or discussion and the only reason for not talking to the mother/ hanging her up after a discussion, was the addiction of the game.<br>
<br>
The possibility the players didnt believe her she was his mother, of just didnt have the password, or didnt want to give her the password, (for obvious reasons, everyone could call and say im XYZs mom) is much closer to reality. As it is much closer to reality that those people talked to her and told her that i listed above.<br>
<br>
Basicaly the report is very subjektive, making the online games or video games in generall the big evil ignorring possible possible other causes of the suicide. Some one mentioned possible reasons allready above and i agree on those. I also think that this person had a somewhat lagging feeling of self respect and self confidence because of his mother not accepting his hobby and partiely life. He seeked gratitude and found acceptance in the online community. When this community betraided him (one player stole money fom him) his world broke and he saw no other exit.<br>
<br>
A sad story indeed, but the article doesnt even tell half of it<br>
